hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Parameterize the rates:
   $$R_{dn}=f\,R_{dd},\quad R_{dp}=(1-f)\,R_{dd},\quad R_{dd}=\text{const}.$$
   Hence
   $$\ln R_{dn}=\ln f+\ln R_{dd},\quad \ln R_{dp}=\ln(1-f)+\ln R_{dd}.$$
2. Differentiate with respect to $\ln f$:
   $$\frac{d\ln R_{dn}}{d\ln f}=1,\qquad 
     \frac{d\ln R_{dp}}{d\ln f}=\frac{d\ln(1-f)}{d\ln f}
     =\frac{d\ln(1-f)}{df}\frac{df}{d\ln f}
     =-\frac1{1-f}\,f=-\frac{f}{1-f}.$$
3. For any abundance $X$, 
   $$d\ln (X/\text{H})=S_{dn}^X\,d\ln R_{dn}+S_{dp}^X\,d\ln R_{dp}.$$
   Thus
   $$\frac{d\ln(\mathrm D/\mathrm H)}{d\ln f}
     =S^D_{dn}-\frac{f}{1-f}\,S^D_{dp},\quad
     \frac{d\ln({}^7\mathrm{Li}/\mathrm H)}{d\ln f}
     =S^{L_7}_{dn}-\frac{f}{1-f}\,S^{L_7}_{dp}.$$
4. Therefore
   $$\frac{d\ln({}^7\mathrm{Li}/\mathrm H)}{d\ln(\mathrm D/\mathrm H)}
     =\frac{S^{L_7}_{dn}-\frac{f}{1-f}S^{L_7}_{dp}}
           {S^D_{dn}-\frac{f}{1-f}S^D_{dp}}
     =\frac{(1-f)\,S^{L_7}_{dn}-f\,S^{L_7}_{dp}}
           {(1-f)\,S^D_{dn}-f\,S^D_{dp}}\Bigg|_{f=f_0}.$$

1. In quasi-static equilibrium (QSE), the abundance of $^7$Be satisfies
$$n_{^3\text{He}}\,n_{^4\text{He}}\langle\sigma v\rangle_{p}
 \;=\;n_{n}\,N_{^7\text{Be}}\,\langle\sigma v\rangle_{d}\,.$$
2. Since light-nuclei densities $n_{^3\text{He}}, n_{^4\text{He}}, n_n$ are unchanged to first order in $\epsilon$, 
$$N_{^7\text{Be}}\propto\frac{\langle\sigma v\rangle_{p}}{\langle\sigma v\rangle_{d}}
 \propto T_b^{\,\nu_p-\nu_d}\,.$$
3. The final $^7$Li/H tracks $N_{^7\text{Be}}$, so
$$\frac{N_{^7\text{Li}}/N_\text{H}}{(N_{^7\text{Li}}/N_\text{H})_{\rm std}}
 =\Bigl(\frac{T_b}{T_\gamma}\Bigr)^{\nu_p-\nu_d}
 =(1+\epsilon)^{\nu_p-\nu_d}\,.$$
4. To first order in $\epsilon$, 
$$(1+\epsilon)^{\nu_p-\nu_d}-1\approx(\nu_p-\nu_d)\,\epsilon\,.$$
Thus the fractional change is $(\nu_p-\nu_d)\epsilon$.
